13.1 What does Ef mean?
=======================

“Ef” is a Greek word (ευ), commonly used as a prefix to denote something
good, nice, and/or easy.  For example, eftopia (ευτοπία) is the opposite
of dystopia (δυστοπία): a good place as opposed to a bad place.


